This great enigma, an emotion entrenched within all of our spirits that defies explanation. I have no use for caring about a daughter I didn't raise to fill my shoes. I have no use caring for a hole which I used to spawn my children. And yet I do. In some incomprehensible sense, we are bound by love. Ever since your mother died, I have made it my life's work to become the villain. I am barred from love to achieve my purposes. And yet... I miss it so dearly. I want to be the father you once loved. I want to become a person someone could love. I know it's useless, and yet every inch of my being demands it. Thankfully, I don't know how to achieve it. I think you do. When I see that witch who hangs beside you, I see your mother again. Alive. I detest that I do, but it is the case. That perfume of yours, I've heard some rumours.
